The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's efforts to combat human trafficking. It states that human trafficking is a modern and barbaric form of exploitation that has no place in the world. The article mentions the Allow States and Victims to Fight Online Sex Trafficking Act of 2017 (FOSTA), which includes the Stop Enabling Sex Traffickers Act of 2017 (SESTA). This legislation aims to provide law enforcement and victims with new tools to fight sex trafficking. The article emphasizes that human sex trafficking is an epidemic and highlights the signing of FOSTA as a continuation of President Trump's efforts to combat human traffickers.